# =============================================================================
# BACKEND .DOCKERIGNORE
# =============================================================================
# This file tells Docker which files/directories to exclude when building
# the image. This makes builds faster and images smaller.
#
# Why use .dockerignore?
#   1. Faster builds: Less data to send to Docker daemon
#   2. Smaller images: Don't include unnecessary files
#   3. Security: Don't accidentally include secrets or credentials
#   4. Cache efficiency: Avoid cache invalidation from irrelevant changes
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# GIT
# =============================================================================
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# =============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION
# =============================================================================
*.md
!README.md
docs/
LICENSE

# =============================================================================
